<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-09-28T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-09-28T11:00:00-05:00" n="602" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d602">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363/478: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-09-28T11:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">September 28,
                                        1928—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 1:10
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>110. The Senate committee unanimously approved article 2 of petroleum
                            bill with following addition: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Therefore the competent authority may decree on petition of a
                                    legitimately interested party the expropriations necessary for
                                    the exercise and development of said industry.”</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Matthews</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>